<html><!-- Newton.html                                      8/25/09 --><!-- This visualization tool was written to accompany         --><!-- A Balanced Introduction to Computer Science, 3rd ed. by  --><!-- David Reed (davereed@creighton.edu), Prentice Hall, 2010 --><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=ISO-8859-1">
  <title> Newton's Algorithm for sqrt w. errs</title>
  <script type="text/javascript">
    function nextNewton(number, guess)
    // Assumes: guess is an estimate of the square root of number
    // Returns: the next (improved) guess using Newton's method
    {
        return (guess + number/guess)/2;
    }
  </script>
</head>

<body>
<div style="text-align:center">
  <h3>Newton's Square Root Algorithm with errors</h3>
  <h3>Visualization Tool to Accompany <br>
  <a href="http://balance3e.com/">A Balanced Introduction to Computer 
Science, 3rd ed.</a><br>David Reed, Prentice Hall, © 2010.</h3>
</div>

  <p>In order to approximate the square root of some number N, Newton's algorithm 
  starts with an initial approximation of 1, <br>
  then repeatedly refines the approximation by averaging the old approximation with N over the old approximation.<br>
  More succinctly,

</p><xmp>
    newApproximation =  (oldApproximation + N/oldApproximation)/2
</xmp>

<p>To see  Newton's algorithm in action, enter the number for which you want to 
compute the square root, then click the button to see each successive 
approximation. 

</p><p></p><hr>

  Find the square root of: 
  <input type="text" id="numberBox" size="8" value="100"
      onchange="document.getElementById('guessBox').value=1;
	        document.getElementById('countBox').value=1;
		document.getElementById('outputDiv').innerHTML='';">
				   
  <input type="hidden" id="guessBox" value="1">
  <input type="hidden" id="countBox" value="1">
  <p>
  <input type="button" value="Get next approximation"
      onclick="document.getElementById('outputDiv').innerHTML +=
		'approximation ' + document.getElementById('countBox').value + ' = ' + 
		document.getElementById('guessBox').value + '<br>' +
		'<tt>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;absolute error:</tt>' +
		(Math.sqrt(parseFloat(document.getElementById('numberBox').value)) - document.getElementById('guessBox').value ) + '<br>' +
		'<tt>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;relative error:</tt>' +
		(Math.sqrt(parseFloat(document.getElementById('numberBox').value)) - document.getElementById('guessBox').value ) / Math.sqrt(parseFloat(document.getElementById('numberBox').value)) +
		'<br>';
		document.getElementById('guessBox').value =
		nextNewton(parseFloat(document.getElementById('numberBox').value),
		parseFloat(document.getElementById('guessBox').value));
		document.getElementById('countBox').value =  
		parseFloat(document.getElementById('countBox').value) + 1;">
  
  <input type="button" value="Clear"
      onclick="document.getElementById('guessBox').value=1;
               document.getElementById('countBox').value=1;
	       document.getElementById('outputDiv').innerHTML='';">
  </p><p>				  
  </p><div id="outputDiv"></div>



</body></html>
